&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welsh Student Nurses must apply via the Student Streamlining Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AMU ASSESSMENT REGISTERED NURSE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have the leadership skills to be a part of an exciting and dynamic new ambulatory emergency care model, focusing on patients with acute medical conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new AMU Assessment Unit that opened early November 2019 is looking for a Full-Time Registered Nurse to support their new ambulatory emergency care assessment unit. This consists of an assessment triage area, treatment chairs, trolleys and acute frailty inpatient beds caring for the acutely ill older person with a variety of medical conditions. Our aim is always to provide high quality of care within a challenging and proactive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will become part of the newly formed Emergency Care Directorate where you will be valued and supported to complete nurse led interventions within a multi-disciplinary structured approach. Ensuring we provide the best possible patient outcomes and positive patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A multi disciplinary team will be readily available in order to help increase your skill set, enhance your knowledge and provide training to enable you to become a valued and essential part of a friendly, supportive and proactive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, enthusiastic and caring individuals who are passionate about providing the highest quality of care to acuity ill patients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any further information or an informal chat please contact Ward Manager Sharon Phillips on 01978 291100 extension 5444 or email Sharon.phillips4@wales.nhs.uk or Emergency Care Matron Claire Headland on 01978 291100 extension 5482/bleep 5321 or email Claire.headland@wales.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 16/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Claire Headland&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information, please contact the recruitment team on 01745448788 (ext. 7606) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
